nfrewshire, Scotland":"苏格兰雷福福爾牛頓 米亞恩斯","lifeSummary":"当Baron Roland de Mearns于1124年出生在苏格兰雷福福爾牛頓 米亞恩斯时，他的父亲Reinald McGaughan30岁，母亲Countess Jean of Mearns25岁。他于大约1169年与Baroness Jonat Sinclair在苏格兰雷福福爾牛頓 米亞恩斯结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1204年之后在他的家乡。"},"hr":{"1124–after 1204":"1124.–nakon 1204.","1124–1204":"1124.–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193.","1170–1203":"1170.–1203.","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187.","1187":"1187.","1095":"1095","1193":"1193.","1170":"1170.","after 1204":"nakon 1204.","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203.","1124":"1124.","about 1127":"oko 1127.","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"oko 1169.","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"cs":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–po 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"po 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"okolo 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"okolo 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"da":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–efter 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"efter 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"omkring 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"omkring 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Skotland","Scotland":"Skotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Skotland"},"nl":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–na 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"na 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"circa 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"circa 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Schotland"},"en":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–after 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"after 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"about 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"about 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Mearns","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the district of The Mearns, an alternative name for Kincardineshire, or from Mearns in Renfrewshire. The placenames derive from Gaelic <i>An Mhaoirne</i> ‘the Stewartry, area under the jurisdiction of a steward’, and is also known to have been adopted in Ireland for <b>Ó Mearáin</b>, see   Marron  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Marron","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Jesus, Armando, Juan, Mario, Carlos, Enrique, Joaquin, Rafael, Alfonso, Alfredo, Alvaro.  Irish Ciaran, Parnell.","Irish (Monaghan): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Mearáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Mearán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>mear</i> ‘lively’. Compare   Merry  . There may have been some confusion with   Marrin  .","Spanish (<b>Marrón</b>): nickname from <i>marrón</i> ‘brown’, a word of French origin."]},{"name":"Marn","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant of <b>Marne</b>, which is perhaps a variant of   Mearns   with loss of final <i>-s</i> or else possibly a variant of   Morrin   1.","Slovenian: nickname from an old spelling of the archaic adjective <i>maren</i> meaning ‘diligent’, but also ‘worthless’. Compare   Maren  ."]}]},{"name":"Roland","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, territory’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. In Old French literature it is borne by a legendary Frankish hero, a vassal of Charlemagne, whose exploits are told in the <i>Chanson de Roland</i>. The subject of the poem is Roland's death at the Battle of Roncesvalles in the Pyrenees in  778 , while protecting the rearguard of the Frankish army on its retreat from Spain. Roland is depicted in literature and legend as headstrong and impulsive. His devoted friendship with the prudent  Oliver  is also legendary."],"variants":[{"name":"Rowland","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roland  , or a transferred use of the surname derived from that given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baron Roland de Mearns was born in 1124, in Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland, his father, Reinald McGaughan, was 30 and his mother, Countess Jean of Mearns, was 25. He married Baroness Jonat Sinclair about 1169, in Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1204, in his hometown."},"et":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–pärast 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"pärast 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"umbes 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"umbes 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–1204 jälkeen","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"1204 jälkeen","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"noin 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"noin 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1124–after 1204":"1124–après 1204","1124–1204":"1124–1204","1134–1193":"1134–1193","1170–1203":"1170–1203","1095–1127":"1095–1127","1100–1187":"1100–1187","1187":"1187","1095":"1095","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","after 1204":"après 1204","1127":"1127","1204":"1204","1203":"1203","1124":"1124","about 1127":"environ 1127","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","about 1169":"environ 1169","Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Newton Mearns, Renfrewshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Mearns, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"